By AHMED KAIGAMA BAUCHI- The National Secretariat of the New Nigeria People Party (NNPP) has suspended indefinitely, its Bauchi State Acting Chairman, Alhaji Sani Shehu, for alleged gross misconduct.The North East Zonal Secretary of the party, Alhaji Babayo Liman, made the announcement at a news briefing on Wednesday in Bauchi.Liman said the acting chairman was suspended because he also lacked commitment to the ideals of the party and showed disrespect and complete arrogance to the party’s national, zonal, state officials.He said that after reviewing the allegations against the state acting chairman, he was issued a query, but he refused to collect it.“He refused to collect the query and we had no other option than to suspend him from office to move the party forward,” Liman said.When contacted, Shehu said he was not aware of the said suspension.“I am not aware and I have nothing to do with the said suspension. Therefore, I remain the acting chairman of the party in Bauchi state,” he said. (NAN) By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Two Senators from Bauchi and Imo States, have resigned their membership of the All Progressives Congress (APC) and Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), respectively. The lawmakers are Senator Dauda Jika representing Bauchi Central and elected on the platform of the APC; and Senator Ezenwa… In "Top Stories" By YAKUBU UBA MAIDUGURI- The Borno Chairman of New Nigerian People’s Party (NNPP), Mr Mohammed Mustafa, said the party had registered over two million members and supporters in the stateMustafa told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Maiduguri on Sunday that the party was very popular in Borno and… In "Politics" By AHMED KAIGAMA •Retired Air Marshal Saddique Abubakar BAUCHI- Former Chief of Air Staff, retired Air Marshal, Saddique Abubakar, has emerged the All Progressives Congress (APC) governoship candidate for 2023 general election in Bauchi State.Abubakar, who is Nigerian Ambassador to Benin Republic, polled 370 votes to defeat s